item.title: [+684] Bribes Let Kraft Sell Tainted Food
item.description: Robert Watson, a top ingredient buyer for Kraft Foods, needed $20,000 to pay his taxes. So he called a broker for a California tomato processor that for years had been paying him bribes to get its products into Kraft’s plants. Prosecutors say SK Foods not only paid off buyers in exchange for contracts but also hid problems like mold.
